name: Five career bundle
description: Collection - Five career bundle - five_career_bundle_0001

name: Mask of the Shadow-Slayer
description: Garb worn by the Shades of the Ashen Hills, whose footfalls leave no sound, and whose blades slice through armour as cleanly as skin.

name: Bakbok
description: Helm favoured by ironbreakers who prefer to settle their arguments face-to-face and brow-to-brow.

name: Purist's Stovepipe
description: Note how the ears are muffled, so the righteous seeker be not distracted by his quarry's perfidious lies...

name: Incandescent Brand
description: Borne by only the most adept at the pyromantic arts, it is said to reflect purity of the devotion to Aqshy.

name: Memento Furioso
description: One simply cannot meet the eyes of this death mask without experiencing foreknowledge of a fiery, fiery death.

name: Fulminator's Crown
description: Metal is said to dampen a wizard's connection to the Winds of Magic, so only a truly accomplished pyromancer can wear such a crown.

name: The Golden Taurox
description: Tauroxes are stubborn, belligerent and almost impossible to stop once they get going. Remind you of anyone?

name: The Anvil of Doom
description: Despite being named for an ancient dawi war machine, we don't recommend hitting this with a hammer ... unless you're well out of the wearer's reach.

name: The Iron Mohawk
description: Beset by shameful baldness? Unable to dye your locks to a brilliant, death-defying orange? Never fear. A few nails, and you'll be as fearsome a slayer as ever there was.

name: Trophy of the Gave
description: Proof that the wearer has survived (indeed, flourished) in battle with the forest-lurking beastmen. Smells horrible.

name: Marienburg Bicorne
description: Marienburg has a poor reputation as a nest of pirates and ne'er do wells. A reputation well-earned. Who knows how many times this hat was stolen from previous owners.

name: Scour-Sun Helm
description: The Knights of Blazing Sun hold that nothing evil nor corrupt can endure beneath the sun's gaze. Well, not for long.

name: Stolen Swine
description: We're not really sure about this one, to be honest. Is it Victor's assistant? His lunch? A familiar sent by Sigmar to embody his fulminating rage? No one's dared ask. Much less tried to take it off him.

name: Deathvigil Mask
description: So rumour goes, Deathvigil Hunters are a secret sect belonging to the Order of the Silver Hammer, dirtying their hands with tasks too burdensome for even the witch hunters.

name: Aspect of Adanhu
description: A mummer's mask, worn at festivals to recount the legends of Athel Loren. Embodies nobility, wisdom and sacrifice.

name: Executioner's Helm
description: Mask worn by those steeped in the mysteries of Khaine. Denotes an individual best kept at arms length, and never out of sight.

name: Wildrunner's Helm
description: Helm once belong to a knight of Avelorn, having met unfortunate end in the Everqueen's service. His whispers still echo through the steel.

name: Naggarond Backstabber
description: Assassin's garb, worn by the particularly untrustworthy (distinctions matter in Naggaroth).

name: Marshal Ludenwald's Favourite Hat
description: Last seen in the vaults of the Emperor Karl-Franz himself. Kruber swears he doesn't know how it ended up in his quarters.

name: Hellequin's Raiment
description: Showy (if tattered) soldier's garb, commissioned from Guisaume of Parravon by an unknown mercenary captain.

name: Friedhelm's Flamboyance
description: Apparently the feathers are magical, though who made it so - and for what purpose - have long been lost to the mists of time.

name: Gambler's Glamour
description: A beautifully-cut suit of rich cloth, designed to dazzle. No doubt purchased with crooked coin.

name: Gungasti
description: Redoubtable helm, named for the rare dwarfen musical instrument to which its horns owe strange similarity.

name: Valaya's Hearthguard
description: Gilded armour of a dawi ironbreaker who stands ever ready to defend his hearth and home.

name: Candlevane Collar
description: Somehow, these candles don't melt when the wizard is at her work. Probably best not to wonder what they're made of.

name: Judge of Myrmidia
description: Cross not Myrmidia's judges, for their verdict is seldom favourable, and their sentence always involves fire.

name: Brazier Crown
description: A fetching wizardly accoutrement, allowing the wearer to better channel fickle Aqshy... and to be seen for miles around, in the right conditions.

name: Wizard's Motley
description: Attire of a Tilea court wizard, hurriedly repurposed for more practical endeavours than flattery.

name: Reaver's Helm
description: Helm of the famed Ellyrian Reavers, who are either bold knights or merciless raiders, depending on at which end of the spear you find yourself.

name: Daughter of Lileath
description: Garb befitting a priestess of the moon goddess, proven in faith and battle.

name: Manann's Favour
description: The stench alone is enough to kill a charging orc. But if times grow desperate, it's good to have a meal close to hand (or head).

name: Redemptive One
description: There's no such thing as standard flagellant's garb... but if there was, this would definitely be it.

name: Soothsayer's Skullcap
description: Traditionally worn by those with a close connection with Ghur, the Wind of Beasts, or else a fondness for mutton stew.

name: Herald of King Taal
description: Regal garb of one who has chosen without doubt his devotion to the Lord of Beasts.

name: Long Drong's Favourite Hat
description: Sadly, no one's entirely clear what happened to the parrot… though there's talk of a rum marinade.

name: Slayer Pirate's Garb
description: There be plunder across them thar seas, dawri!

name: Forebear's Helm
description: Treasured heirloom of an ancient elven house - one that has survived the centuries where the associated bloodline has not.

name: Herald of the Weave
description: Garb granted to a true champion of Athel Loren, and a foremost protector of the Weave

name: Beast-Hunter's Hat
description: Headgear of a templar well-accustomed to tracking down the accursed Children of Chaos, wherever they may hide.

name: Helhunten's Hauberk
description: Raiment of an (in)famous slayer of undead, Joseph von Helhunten. A man not to be crossed, be you unliving or no.

name: Griffon Crown
description: Treasured helm belonging to a long dead member of the Order of the Knights Griffon.

name: Knight Griffon
description: Armour hailing from the Imperial Knights Griffon, a templar order founded from a valiant sect of the Knights Panther.

name: Immolator's Casket
description: Some fury cannot be tamed, only caged. When the wizard is about her work, the air stinks of hot metal and seared flesh.

name: Blazing Soul Raiment
description: Even for Bright Wizards, this garb suggests the primary purpose is containment, rather than clothing.

name: Kahirn
description: Imposing helm of a style popular throughout the Worlds Edge Mountains. Best to walk sideways through narrow doors.

name: Varagvlag
description: The wolf-pelt armour of a lone ranger, possibly an outcast from his hold. Very warm, even in the coldest climes.

name: Kossar's Crown
description: By tradition, a hat only worn by a hunter who has wrestled a bear into submission and lived to tell of it.

name: Wulfhart's Array
description: Hunting garb of one Markus Wulfhart, monster slayer and huntsmarshal of the Empire. Practical garb for a practical man.

name: Scholar's Lantern Helm
description: Headgear favoured by Bright Wizards who like to see where they're going, and be seen in return.

name: Seeker's Robes
description: The vestments of a tireless scholar, steeped in the mysteries of turbulent Aqshy.

name: Galazklad
description: Magnificent example of the armoursmith's trade, fashioned by the master armourer Bruk Brokkisson.

name: Chracian Lion Helm
description: Headgear of a White Lion of Chrace - renowned royal bodyguards of Ulthuan and peerless woods-walkers.

name: Chracian Valourguard
description: Garb of a White Lion guardian in service to the fabled prince Temakador. Nice lad, so I hear.

name: Ratechism
description: Belonging to an unofficial sect (with a single deluded member). He holds that Sigmar's will is clearly communicated through the squeaks of unmutated rats.

name: Flagellant of the Twin-Tailed Comet
description: Worn by one whose devotion to Sigmar and sanity are seldom questioned, though for different reasons.

name: Flame Within
description: Naught kindles a flame like the soul of its conjurer ... but once it takes root, beware.

name: Maven's Cindergarb
description: This gown has clearly been too close to a flame ... but did that flame burn without, or within?

name: Ranger's Tattered Patch
description: This item has seen better days - much like the unfortunate who has donned it.

name: Ranger's Wilds-Worn Garb
description: Well-loved and now, alas, approaching the end of its days, this armour will still serve in a pinch.

name: Candelight Helm
description: Jury-rigged miner's helm. More notable for its practicality than its functionality.

name: Reikland Rover
description: This garb has a decidedly Bretonnian cut to its cloth, though an Imperial bounty hunter would surely never don such an outfit.

name: Myrmidia's Gaze
description: Not an easy stare to meet. But don't blink - you might lose your head.

name: Armour of the Blazing Sun
description: Full plate blessed by the goddess Myrmidia, and thus dedicated to the cause of justice.

name: Drakira's Grin
description: Mask of a Naggarothi corsair. Not the most practical of garb, but you'll linger in folks' memories for a fair old while.

name: Dreadguard's Mantle
description: Intimidating armour worn by a favourite of Malekith's court - a position that seldom offers longevity.

name: The Crown of Avelorn (Facsimile)
description: Or so it purports to be. Alas, it seems likely that the Everqueen's handmaidens would have something pointed to express about its apparent purloinment.

name: High Robes of Isha (Counterfeit)
description: Raiment that marks the wearer as among the highest of Isha's devotees in the mortal realm. This is no proof of passivity, however, as sometimes healing can only occur after bloodshed.

name: Angrund Helm (Possibly)
description: Almost certainly not the actual helm of Belegar Ironhammer, but close enough in design for someone wishing to bask in his reflected glory.

name: Angrundklad (Perhaps)
description: Armour modelled after that worn by the famed Belegar Ironhammer of Karak Eight Peaks ... though is likely not as battered as the real thing.

name: Headband of Huss (Almost Certainly)
description: Luthor Huss has fallen on hard times lately, but fortunately his circlet has found its way into faithful hands.

display_type: Warrior Priest of Sigmar Hero Skin
name: Prophet's Armour (Poetic Licence Taken)
description: While it's not definitively recorded that Luthor Huss ever wore purple, nor is it definitively recorded that he never wore purple. For Lohner's supplier, that's ambiguity enough.

name: Gormann's Cindercage (Salvaged)
description: Quite what became of Thyrus Gormann remains a mystery. His battle garb, however, has surely outlasted him.

name: Patriarch's Finery (Slight Seconds)
description: It is said that Thyrus Gormann possessed a deep, but alas unvaried, wardrobe. A great mind disdains trivia such as "what a fellow is to wear today".

name: Crown of the True King (Possibly Genuine)
description: Though at first blush it might seem unlikely that Kruber has managed to get his hands on Louen Leoncouer's crown, Kruber is Kruber and this is an exceedingly nice bit of headgear.

name: Raiment of the True King (Unverified)
description: Bears the unmistakeable heraldry of Louen Leoncouer, King of Bretonnia, in whose land such impersonation would carry the gravest of penalties.

name: Tri-Skull Crown
description: A Bright Wizard seldom has a shortage of skulls close to hand, although most will need wiping clean first.

name: The Lost Helm of Karak-Hirn
description: I don't know. Can't put a thing down for five minutes without someone stealing it and putting it up for sale…

name: Sneaker's Helm
description: Some hunters believe that adopting a fox as their totem makes them sneakier. It certainly makes them look distinctive when seen.

name: Gladiatorial Gaze
description: There's no mistaking the gilded mask of one who pledges themselves to Eldrazor, the Lord of Blades.

name: Tax Collector's Cap
description: Always have a dagger close to hand. You never know when someone's going to seek a rebate.

name: Agent of Malekith
description: Cloak yourself in the shadows and seek out the Witch-King's foes ... or just kill lots of Pactsworn for the fun of it. They make such pretty noises when they die.

name: Flamboyant Sellsword
description: There's no shame in being a mercenary. In fact, why not display a little bit of every uniform you've ever worn? Might remind some folk that you're on their side.

name: Dashing Rogue
description: Never let it be said that you're not one to strut your stuff, should the situation call for it. Derring-do? Optional. Rakish wist? Something of a work in progress.

name: Karak Norn Hold-Keeper
description: Take up your runic armour and stand firm against those who'd despoil your hearth and home. A rousing song wouldn't hurt neither, dawri.

name: Light of Judgement
description: So much injustice in the world. So much intolerance. Well, it's time to light a candle or two in Myrmidia's name and burn the injust and intolerant to ash, darlings.

name: Lohner's Collections
description: <five_career_bundle_0001_desc>

name: Molten Motley
description: Garb fit for the most magmatic of magicians. Unleash the fury of Aqshy in inimitable style.

name: Ellyrian Handmaiden
description: Don the garb of a temple handmaiden of Ellyrian; stern, austere and unflinching before those who would threaten Ulthuan.

name: Acolyte of Sea & Storm
description: Though the shipwreck drowned your companions, Sigmar has saved you for a higher purpose - one steeped in skaven blood.

name: Taal's Huntsman
description: Embrace your inner beast and roam the Stirland wilderness as a champion of King Taal.

name: Long Drong's Landlubber
description: It's time to set sail for plunder with the famed slayer pirates. Or it would be, if there was any sign of their ship.

name: Lohner's Brauzeit Collection
description: Multi-character collection

name: Wild Heath Warden
description: Sentinel of Athel Loren's wild border, where ancient waystones contain the wrath of hungry trees.

name: Elithis Pilgrimage
description: Vestments of a Witch Hunter determined to seek out heretics in distant lands. No word of his success (or failure) has ever reached the Empire.

name: Templar Herald
description: Armour of a knight charged with carrying Sigmar's message into the distant crusading lands of Araby. Judging by its condition, he was not well received.

name: Molten Soul
description: Ensorcelled raiment of a wizard determined to walk the weave of Aqshy. Mostly fireproof, though the same cannot alas be said of the wearer.

name: Vargza
description: Garb of a dispossessed king, doomed to wander the Worlds Edge Mountain in search of a home he can never reclaim.

name: Huntsmarshal's Raiment
description: When wandering the wilds, one should do so in style ... and wearing the odd trophy doesn't hurt.

name: Robes of the Illuminator
description: Mariah Holsrieke was famed for bringing light to challenging subjects both philosophical and physical ... many of which burned to ash beneath her scrutiny.

name: Defender of the Eight Peaks
description: Hofni Haraldson defended Karak Eight Peaks to his last breath. There are heroes, even in the dark.

name: Phoenix King's Bodyguard
description: Garb of Alvani Silestta, a Chracian White Lion tasked with protecting the ruler of Ulthuan in life or through death.

name: Sigmar's Prophet
description: Tattered rags once belonging to Gerhardt Wulf, the self-proclaimed Prophet of Sigmar. Welcome on the battlefield, less so in more civilised climes.

name: Wanderers in the Wild Collection
description: Clad your favorite hero in the garb of a seasoned traveller. The Wanderers in the Wild collection contains 10 premium cosmetics - one skin and one hat for each playable hero - inspired by forebears who forsook their homes for adventure in distant lands.

name: Unsung Heroes Collection
description: Grab yourself a new set of armour and honour the Unsung Heroes of the world.  The Unsung Heroes Collection contains 10 premium cosmetics - one skin and one hat for each playable hero - inspired by heroes whose feats deserve to be heard.

name: Burning Soul
description: A wizard can conjure the flame for only so long before succumbing to its embrace.

name: Rambling Ranger
description: Who can say the last time this wandering dawi last graced the doors of his hold?

name: Relentless Reiklander
description: Practical and cost effective attire for a roving bounty hunter.

name: Knight of the Blazing Sun
description: Glorious raiment worn by a preceptor of the Blazing Sun. Forever a beacon of light and hope.

name: Dreadlord's Array
description: Cursed armour from distant Naggaroth. The previous owner hasn't a use for it any longer.

name: Absent Friends Collection
description: Lohner claims these clothes once belonged to old allies of his, but refuses to offer up details. Is it some kind of cunning sales technique on his part?

name: Alarielle the Radiant
description: Flowing raiment fit for one who would seek to embrace the grace of the peerless Everqueen of Avelorn.

name: Belegar Ironhammer
description: Battle-ready garb for any bold dawi seeking to embody as the stalwart reclaimer of Karak Eight Peaks.

name: Luthor Huss
description: While to directly imitate the Prophet of Valten would be considered tantamount to heresy, honouring his memory - if only in part - attracts less suspicion.

name: Thyrus Gormann
description: Cloth and collar designed to transform the wearer into the clear inheritor of the once-supreme patriarch's mantle.

name: Louen Leoncouer
description: Armour and heraldry fit for a King of Bretonnia ... or one who would be thought so.

name: Heroic Masquerade
description: Five consumate conjurations of the costumer's art designed to transform battle-weary warriors into the greatest heroes this world - or any other - has seen.

name: Helms of the Valorous
description: You're sure to turn heads as you take to the streets of the Old World in these dashing hats.

name: Ritual Hearth Tattoo
description: The line between magical runes and dawi art is betimes a slender one. If asked, Bardin insists that these help keep out the cold.

name: Protection of the Peaks
description: Slayers may not hold with the principle of clothes in a general sense, but there's nothing glorious about dying of frostbite, by Grimnir!

name: Winterskins
description: There is more than meets the eye to the symbolic fur and runic tattoo that keeps a Slayer from freezing to death in the high places of the world, there is a tenacious and unyielding will to endure!

name: Atylwyth Crown
description: Traditional garb of the Winterheart's waywatchers, who also serve as custodians of the realm's oldest folk tales.

name: Atylwyth Chanter's Robe
description: There are many wintertime tales of Athel Loren, and year upon year the chanter-smiths of Atylwyth recount them all by crisp starlight.

name: Atylwyth Rime Master
description: Tis said the wisest of Atylwyth's waywatchers can track a single snowflake through a blizzard, and sing-chant lore songs that can thaw the coldest of hearts.

name: Wolverheart Crown
description: Where the wolves of Ulric hunt, the followers of Chaos beware.

name: Wolverheart Furs
description: A garb beloved of Ulric perhaps, but once the snows fall its warmth is as valued as the Winter God's favour.

name: Blessings of the White Wolf
description: As winter is harsh and unforgiving, so too is Ulric. Yet those who bear his favour feel not winter's bite.

name: Solstice Warden's Hood
description: The sting of frozen metal against the cheek is merely another trial to bear in Sigmar's name.

name: Solstice Warden's Garb
description: Sigmarites seldom wrap up against the cold as well as they should, likely because doing so would be seen as granting Ulricans a small victory.

name: Solstice Warden's Forbearance
description: The fortitude of righteousness offers, if not warmth or comfort, then at least forbearance to tolerant that which by duty must be borne.

name: Midwinter Tines
description: How the candles do not blow out in in the freezing gales of year's end is anyone's guess. Magic, certainly ... but of what kind?

name: Midwinter Flammengarb
description: Enchanted to retain an echo of Aqshy's warmth in even the coldest climes, these furs are a danger to anything combustible.

name: Flammenbringer
description: To bear even a flicker of the flame eternal is to stand proof against the harshest winds of winter.

name: Frost-Guard Collection
description: Protect thyself from the fell winds of winter. The Frost-Guard Collection contains 10 cosmetics - one skin and one hat for each playable hero - because your looks should slay, even in the season of sleigh!
